{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "In [19] the authors compare BERT with ChatGPT on a few-shots approach, using the GLUE benchmark, but the intent classification task is not represented there.",
    "A similar comparison using ChatGPT on few-shots learning and a fine-tuned BERT for sentiment analysis is performed in [20], but it also misses a fine-tuned version of a decoder-only architecture, and the intent classification task.",
    "A comprehensive study in sentiment analysis is carried out in [21] but they only use encoder-decoder or decoder-only architectures.",
    "In [22] the authors explore zero and few shots learning on encoder-only models and use GPT-3 as a data augmentation method.",
    "While all these studies provide relevant insights, there is a lack of a study that compares encoderonly and decoder-only architectures on NLU tasks beyond sentiment analysis, such as intent classification."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "In [19] the authors compare BERT with ChatGPT on a few-shots approach, using the GLUE benchmark, but the intent classification task is not represented there.",
